					<marginalia_text>
						Plurimus vsus facetiarum in Conuiuijs, et festiuis Colloquijs: in quibus etiam
						delectant Problemata, qualia in Mensa Philosophica: proposita vrbana, qualia in
						4.to Guatij, et 1.o Castilionis: a[e]nigmata, vulgo <!--JG: Perhaps better to transcribe [quarto] and [primo]-->
					</marginalia_text>
					<person name="Stefano Guazzo"/>
					<person name="Castiglione"/>
					<book title="Mensa philosophica"/>
					<book title="The civil conversation"/>
					<book title="Book of the Courtier"/>
				</position>
			</language>
			<language ident="EN">
				<position place="left_margin" book_orientation="90">
					<marginalia_text>
						riddles.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				There are many uses for jokes at dinner parties or festive gatherings, where even problems
				are delightful, such as those found in the Mensa Philsophia; otherwise, there are urbane propositions, 
				such as those in the fourth book of Guazzi, and the first book of Castiglione; else puzzles, and riddles in the vernacular. 
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
